## MCP Tool References

Add this section after the existing tool routing table:

### Custom MCP Tools (forensic-ai server)

For the following forensic operations, use the MCP tools instead of raw shell commands. They return structured, paginated JSON that prevents context window overflow.

| MCP Tool | Replaces | When to Use |
|---|---|---|
| `vol_pslist` | `python3 vol.py ... windows.pslist.PsList` | Process listing on ANY memory image — always use this instead of shell |
| `vol_netscan` | `python3 vol.py ... windows.netscan.NetScan` | Network connections on ANY memory image — always use this instead of shell |
| `build_supertimeline` | `log2timeline.py` + `psort.py` | Building or querying timelines — MUST use this to avoid millions of raw CSV lines |

For all other forensic tools (malfind, dlllist, handles, cmdline, MFTECmd, EvtxECmd, RECmd, PECmd, YARA, etc.), continue using Protocol SIFT's existing shell access.

---

## Deployment

1. Copy skill files to the Claude Code skills directory:
   ```bash
   mkdir -p ~/.claude/skills/forensic-ai
   cp /path/to/forensic-ai/skills/*.md ~/.claude/skills/forensic-ai/
   ```

2. Add the MCP server to `~/.claude/settings.json` (see `config/settings.json.example`):
   ```bash
   # Edit the existing settings.json to add the mcpServers block
   nano ~/.claude/settings.json
   ```

3. Update the global `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` with the routing table entries above.

4. Restart Claude Code to pick up the new configuration.
